spirit:component.spirit:name: axi_datamover_256MM_32STR
spirit:component.spirit:description: AXI DataMover is a soft Xilinx IP core used as a building block for scalable DMA functions. It provides the basic AXI4 Memory Map Read to AXI4-Stream and AXI4-Stream to AXI4 Memory Map Write data transport and protocol conversion. It supports Synchronous/Asynchronous clocking for Command/Status interface. Supports Memory Map and Stream side data widht up to 1024 bits and Memory Map address width up to 64-bit. AXI Datamover core also provide optional Data Realignment Engine (DRE) upto 64-bit of stream data width, General purpose Store and Forward unit, Interminate BTT mode.

spirit:parameter.spirit:description: Select the type of channel to be used. A Full channel has all the features of Datamover. A Basic channel provides a smaller foot print Datamover with less features. Refer the Product Guide for more details.

spirit:parameter.spirit:name: c_enable_cache_user
spirit:parameter.spirit:description: When enabled, the user can specify the value to be driven on xCACHE and xUSER of AXI4 MM2S and S2MM interfaces. These values can be specified in the command field. When enabled and in Basic mode, these values specified in the command field are neglected and xCACHE signal is tied to 0011 while xUSER is tied to 0000.
